{"id": "1434854688825544744", "channel_id": "1434231598701609092", "type": 4, "author_id": "1131790839291596841", "author_name": "morimensstaff01", "author_bot": false, "content": "💭「Processing」Infinite loading", "timestamp": "2025-11-03T10:40:16.127000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1434231598701609092", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Infinite loading", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168103141416960"]}
{"id": "1435003546616467527", "channel_id": "1435003546616467527", "type": 0, "author_id": "244028747999608832", "author_name": "vxvendetta", "author_bot": false, "content": "A general sentiment i heard from a lot of players is that this boss is very annoying to fight.\nThe fact that in the second phase she get the equivalent of universal 80% damage reduction is pretty frustrating and it doesn't seems justified or offer interesting counterplay opportunities.\nFrom the story, she has 108k hp in phase one, if we don't even count the staking Fortress she get every turn there, after we beat the phase and she become Invulnerable, the second one leave her at 50% hp but Permanent 80 Fortress, that just mean that she now has an equivalent of 250k+ hp, when Tawil, the boss the previous stage had 36k+ in phase 1 and 110k+ in phase 2.\nOne may think that the State card she give you may be used to lower her hp during the second Phase, but in reality it remove only 1600+ hp per card (and give her str), that means that, even if you keep 5 of those (that is not very feasible without giving her a ton of str during the first phase) in hand you will deal only around 8k per turn, so you would need 7 turns to kill her phase 2, but that would mean giving her 55 STR every turn.\n\nWhat is the intended plan in there? \nIt's especially bad when she is in Dtide, because you don't have the Story gimmick to help you, especially bad in higher Alerts.\nEveryone normally cheese her second phase with Aigis stunn and Bleed or other bursts, and even if the interaction is nice, it shouldn't be the intended way to beat it.\nThe team should look it up.\n\nIf someone have potential insights on this battle that i may missing, feel free to share.", "timestamp": "2025-11-03T20:31:46.590000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-03T20:39:58.932000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "grin", "emoji_id": "1400771716665446471", "count": 1}], "attachments": [{"id": "1435003547379826830", "filename": "dasde.JPG", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 43872, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1435003546616467527/1435003547379826830/dasde.JPG?ex=69cc2f32&is=69caddb2&hm=de7cf6aea82501daa23ac2cd5ffdb6c5d23e29267820e4f110140aae5a3cb8fd&"}, {"id": "1435003547786805268", "filename": "sdgg.JPG", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 50290, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1435003546616467527/1435003547786805268/sdgg.JPG?ex=69cc2f32&is=69caddb2&hm=bba6a99e2c1e6c2df644306d84c84d493f865fd05d8819eb396bc4d1e08313a8&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1435003546616467527", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Aisha Boss Fight", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785"]}
